block content 
    h1.bd-title#content Navbar
    p.bd-lead Documentation and examples for Bootstrap’s powerful, responsive navigation header, the navbar. Includes support for branding, navigation, and more, including support for our collapse plugin.
    
    h2#how-it-works How it works
    p Here’s what you need to know before getting started with the navbar:
    ul
        li
            | Navbars require a wrapping 
            code.highlighter-rouge .navbar
            |  with 
            code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-expand{-sm|-md|-lg|-xl}
            |  for responsive collapsing and 
            a(href='#color-schemes') color scheme
            |  classes.
        li
            | Navbars and their contents are fluid by default. Use 
            a(href='#containers') optional containers
            |  to limit their horizontal width.
        li
            | Use our 
            a(href='/docs/utilities/spacing/') spacing
            |  and 
            a(href='/docs/utilities/flex/') flex
            |  utility classes for controlling spacing and alignment within navbars.
        li
            | Navbars are responsive by default, but you can easily modify them to change that. Responsive behavior depends on our Collapse JavaScript plugin.
        li
            | Navbars are hidden by default when printing. Force them to be printed by adding 
            code.highlighter-rouge .d-print
            |  to the 
            code.highlighter-rouge .navbar
            | . See the 
            a(href='/docs/utilities/display/') display
            |  utility class.
        li
            | Ensure accessibility by using a 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;nav&gt;
            |  element or, if using a more generic element such as a 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;div&gt;
            | , add a 
            code.highlighter-rouge role="navigation"
            |  to every navbar to explicitly identify it as a landmark region for users of assistive technologies.
    p Read on for an example and list of supported sub-components.
    h2#supported-content Supported content
    p
        | Navbars come with built-in support for a handful of sub-components. Choose from the following as needed:
    ul
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-brand
            |  for your company, product, or project name.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-nav
            |  for a full-height and lightweight navigation (including support for dropdowns).
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-toggler
            |  for use with our collapse plugin and other 
            a(href='#responsive-behaviors') navigation toggling
            |  behaviors.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge .form-inline
            |  for any form controls and actions.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-text
            |  for adding vertically centered strings of text.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge .collapse.navbar-collapse
            |  for grouping and hiding navbar contents by a parent breakpoint.
    p
        | Here’s an example of all the sub-components included in a responsive light-themed navbar that automatically collapses at the 
        code.highlighter-rouge lg
        |  (large) breakpoint.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            +navbar-menu('navbarSupportedContent')
                +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                    +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                    +nav-item('Link','#')
                    +nav-item-dropdown('Dropdown','#')
                        +dropdown-menu([
                            {text:'Action',data:'#'},
                            {text:'Another action',data:'#'},
                            {},
                            {text:'Something else here',data:'#'},
                        ])
                    +nav-item('Disabled','#','disabled')
            form.form-inline.my-2.my-lg-0
                +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                +btn-outline-success('Search','','submit')
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
                    +navbar-menu('navbarSupportedContent')
                        +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                            +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                            +nav-item('Link','#')
                            +nav-item-dropdown('Dropdown','#')
                                +dropdown-menu([
                                    {text:'Action',data:'#'},
                                    {text:'Another action',data:'#'},
                                    {},
                                    {text:'Something else here',data:'#'},
                                ])
                            +nav-item('Disabled','#','disabled')
                    form.form-inline.my-2.my-lg-0
                        +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                        +btn-outline-success('Search','','submit')

    p
        | This example uses 
        a(href='/docs/utilities/colors/') color
        |  (
        code.highlighter-rouge bg-light
        | ) and 
        a(href='/docs/utilities/spacing/') spacing
        |  (
        code.highlighter-rouge my-2
        | , 
        code.highlighter-rouge my-lg-0
        | , 
        code.highlighter-rouge mr-sm-0
        | , 
        code.highlighter-rouge my-sm-0
        | ) utility classes.
    h3#brand Brand
    p
        | The 
        code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-brand
        |  can be applied to most elements, but an anchor works best as some elements might require utility classes or custom styles.
    .bd-example
        // As a link
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
        // As a heading
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('','Navbar')
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                // As a link
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')

                // As a heading
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('','Navbar')
    p
        | Adding images to the 
        code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-brand
        |  will likely always require custom styles or utilities to properly size. Here are some examples to demonstrate.
    .bd-example
        // Just an image
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','','/assets/images/logo.png','30')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                // Just an image
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','','/assets/images/logo.png','30')
    
    .bd-example
        // Image and text
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','3Forcom','/assets/images/logo.png','30')
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                // Image and text
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','3Forcom','/assets/images/logo.png','30')
    
    h3#nav Nav
    p
        | Navbar navigation links build on our 
        code.highlighter-rouge .nav
        |  options with their own modifier class and require the use of 
        a(href='#toggler') toggler classes
        |  for proper responsive styling. 
        strong
            | Navigation in navbars will also grow to occupy as much horizontal space as possible
        |  to keep your navbar contents securely aligned.
    p
        | Active states—with 
        code.highlighter-rouge .active
        | —to indicate the current page can be applied directly to 
        code.highlighter-rouge .nav-link
        | s or their immediate parent 
        code.highlighter-rouge .nav-item
        | s.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            +navbar-menu('navbarNav')
                +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                    +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                    +nav-item('Features','#')
                    +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                    +nav-item('Disabled','#','disabled')
    
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
                    +navbar-menu('navbarNav','mr-auto')
                        +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                        +nav-item('Features','#')
                        +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                        +nav-item('Disabled','#','disabled')

    p
        | And because we use classes for our navs, you can avoid the list-based approach entirely if you like.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            +navbar-menu('navbarNav')
                .navbar-nav
                    a.nav-item.nav-link.active(href='#')
                        | Home 
                        span.sr-only (current)
                    a.nav-item.nav-link(href='#') Features
                    a.nav-item.nav-link(href='#') Pricing
                    a.nav-item.nav-link.disabled(href='#') Disabled
    
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
                    +navbar-menu('navbarNav')
                        .navbar-nav
                            a.nav-item.nav-link.active(href='#')
                                | Home 
                                span.sr-only (current)
                            a.nav-item.nav-link(href='#') Features
                            a.nav-item.nav-link(href='#') Pricing
                            a.nav-item.nav-link.disabled(href='#') Disabled

    p
        | You may also utilize dropdowns in your navbar nav. Dropdown menus require a wrapping element for positioning, so be sure to use separate and nested elements for 
        code.highlighter-rouge .nav-item
        |  and 
        code.highlighter-rouge .nav-link
        |  as shown below.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            +navbar-menu('navbarNavDropdown')
                +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                    +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                    +nav-item('Features','#')
                    +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                    +nav-item-dropdown('Dropdown link','#')
                        +dropdown-menu([
                            {text:'Action',data:'#'},
                            {text:'Another action',data:'#'},
                            {text:'Something else here',data:'#'},
                        ])
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
                    +navbar-menu('navbarNavDropdown')
                        +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                            +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                            +nav-item('Features','#')
                            +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                            +nav-item-dropdown('Dropdown link','#')
                                +dropdown-menu([
                                    {text:'Action',data:'#'},
                                    {text:'Another action',data:'#'},
                                    {text:'Something else here',data:'#'},
                                ])

    h3#forms Forms
    p
        | Place various form controls and components within a navbar with 
        code.highlighter-rouge .form-inline
        | .
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            form.form-inline
                +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                +btn-outline-success('Search','','submit')
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    form.form-inline
                        +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                        +btn-outline-success('Search','','submit')

    p
        | Immediate children elements in 
        code.highlighter-rouge .navbar
        |  use flex layout and will default to 
        code.highlighter-rouge justify-content: between
        | . Use additional 
        a(href='/docs/utilities/flex/') flex utilities
        |  as needed to adjust this behavior.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            form.form-inline
                +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                +btn-outline-success('Search','','submit')
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
                    form.form-inline
                        +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                        +btn-outline-success('Search','','submit')
    
    p Input groups work, too:
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            form.form-inline
                +input-group('@')
                    +input-simple('text','textUsername','Username')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    form.form-inline
                        +input-group('@')
                            +input-simple('text','textUsername','Username')
    
    p
        | Various buttons are supported as part of these navbar forms, too. This is also a great reminder that vertical alignment utilities can be used to align different sized elements.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            form.form-inline
                +btn-outline-success('Main button')
                | &nbsp;
                +btn-outline-sm-secondary('Smaller button')
    
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    form.form-inline
                        +btn-outline-success('Main button')
                        +btn-outline-sm-secondary('Smaller button')

    h3#text Text
    p
        | Navbars may contain bits of text with the help of 
        code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-text
        | . This class adjusts vertical alignment and horizontal spacing for strings of text.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            span.navbar-text Navbar text with an inline element
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    span.navbar-text Navbar text with an inline element

    p Mix and match with other components and utilities as needed.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar w/ text')
            +navbar-menu('navbarText')
                +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                    +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                    +nav-item('Features','#')
                    +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                span.navbar-text Navbar text with an inline element

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Navbar w/ text')
                    +navbar-menu('navbarText')
                        +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                            +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                            +nav-item('Features','#')
                            +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                        span.navbar-text Navbar text with an inline element
    
    h2#color-schemes Color schemes
    p
        | Theming the navbar has never been easier thanks to the combination of theming classes and 
        code.highlighter-rouge background-color
        |  utilities. Choose from 
        code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-light
        |  for use with light background colors, or 
        code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-dark
        |  for dark background colors. Then, customize with 
        code.highlighter-rouge .bg-*
        |  utilities.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            +navbar-menu('navbarColor01')
                +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                    +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                    +nav-item('Features','#')
                    +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                    +nav-item('About','#')
            form.form-inline.my-2.my-lg-0
                +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                +btn-outline-info('Search','','submit')

        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-primary')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            +navbar-menu('navbarColor02')
                +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                    +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                    +nav-item('Features','#')
                    +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                    +nav-item('About','#')
            form.form-inline.my-2.my-lg-0
                +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                +btn-outline-light('Search','','submit')
        
        +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light','background-color: #e3f2fd;')
            +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
            +navbar-menu('navbarColor03')
                +navbar-nav('mr-auto')
                    +nav-item('Home','#','active')
                    +nav-item('Features','#')
                    +nav-item('Pricing','#')
                    +nav-item('About','#')
            form.form-inline.my-2.my-lg-0
                +input-simple('search','textsearch','Search','','mr-sm-2  my-2')
                +btn-outline-primary('Search','','submit')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark')
                    // Navbar content

                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-primary')
                    // Navbar content
                
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light','background-color: #e3f2fd;')
                    // Navbar content
    
    h2#containers Containers
    p
        | Although it’s not required, you can wrap a navbar in a 
        code.highlighter-rouge .container
        |  to center it on a page or add one within to only center the contents of a 
        a(href='#placement') fixed or static top navbar
        | .
    .bd-example
        .container
            +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                .container
                    +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                        +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')

    p
        | When the container is within your navbar, its horizontal padding is removed at breakpoints lower than your specified 
        code.highlighter-rouge .navbar-expand{-sm|-md|-lg|-xl}
        |  class. This ensures we’re not doubling up on padding unnecessarily on lower viewports when your navbar is collapsed.
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            .container
                +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light')
                    .container
                        +navbar-brand('#','Navbar')
    
    h2#placement Placement
    p
        | Use our 
        a(href='/docs/utilities/position/') position utilities
        |  to place navbars in non-static positions. Choose from fixed to the top, fixed to the bottom, or stickied to the top (scrolls with the page until it reaches the top, then stays there). Fixed navbars use 
        code.highlighter-rouge position: fixed
        | , meaning they’re pulled from the normal flow of the DOM and may require custom CSS (e.g., 
        code.highlighter-rouge padding-top
        |  on the 
        code.highlighter-rouge <body>
        | ) to prevent overlap with other elements.
    p
        | Also note that 
        strong
            code.highlighter-rouge .sticky-top
            |  uses 
            code.highlighter-rouge position: sticky
            | , which 
            a(href='https://caniuse.com/#feat=css-sticky') isn’t fully supported in every browser
        | .
    .bd-example
        +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Default')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +navbar('navbar-light bg-light')
                    +navbar-brand('#','Default')

    .bd-example
        +navbar('fixed-top navbar-light bg-light')
            +navbar-brand('#','Fixed top')
    figure.highlight
